{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Well, this is such an honor. And it's wonderful to be"},{"time":6000,"text":"in the presence of an organization that is really making a difference in the world."},{"time":12000,"text":"And I'm intensely grateful for the opportunity to speak to you today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18000,"text":"And I'm also rather surprised, because when I look back on my life"},{"time":25000,"text":"the last thing I ever wanted to do was write, or be in any way involved in religion."},{"time":34000,"text":"After I left my convent, I'd finished with religion, frankly."},{"time":38000,"text":"I thought that was it."},{"time":39000,"text":"And for 13 years I kept clear of it. I wanted to be an English literature professor."},{"time":47000,"text":"And I certainly didn't even want to be a writer, particularly."},{"time":51000,"text":"But then I suffered a series of career catastrophes,"},{"time":56000,"text":"one after the other, and finally found myself in television. (Laughter)"},{"time":66000,"text":"I said that to Bill Moyers, and he said, \"Oh, we take anybody.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":70000,"text":"And I was doing some rather controversial religious programs."},{"time":75000,"text":"This went down very well in the U.K., where religion is extremely unpopular."},{"time":82000,"text":"And so, for once, for the only time in my life, I was finally in the mainstream."},{"time":87000,"text":"But I got sent to Jerusalem to make a film about early Christianity."},{"time":94000,"text":"And there, for the first time, I encountered the other religious traditions:"},{"time":99000,"text":"Judaism and Islam, the sister religions of Christianity."},{"time":104000,"text":"And while I found I knew nothing about these faiths at all --"},{"time":108000,"text":"despite my own intensely religious background,"},{"time":113000,"text":"I'd seen Judaism only as a kind of prelude to Christianity,"},{"time":116000,"text":"and I knew nothing about Islam at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119000,"text":"But in that city, that tortured city,"},{"time":122000,"text":"where you see the three faiths jostling so uneasily together,"},{"time":128000,"text":"you also become aware of the profound connection between them."},{"time":131000,"text":"And it has been the study of other religious traditions that brought me back"},{"time":136000,"text":"to a sense of what religion can be, and actually enabled me"},{"time":140000,"text":"to look at my own faith in a different light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143000,"text":"And I found some astonishing things in the course of my study"},{"time":147000,"text":"that had never occurred to me. Frankly, in the days when I thought I'd had it with religion,"},{"time":154000,"text":"I just found the whole thing absolutely incredible."},{"time":157000,"text":"These doctrines seemed unproven, abstract."},{"time":163000,"text":"And to my astonishment, when I began seriously studying other traditions,"},{"time":170000,"text":"I began to realize that belief -- which we make such a fuss about today --"},{"time":176000,"text":"is only a very recent religious enthusiasm"},{"time":181000,"text":"that surfaced only in the West, in about the 17th century."},{"time":187000,"text":"The word \"belief\" itself originally meant to love, to prize, to hold dear."},{"time":194000,"text":"In the 17th century, it narrowed its focus,"},{"time":198000,"text":"for reasons that I'm exploring in a book I'm writing at the moment,"},{"time":201000,"text":"to include -- to mean an intellectual assent to a set of propositions, a credo."},{"time":210000,"text":"\"I believe:\" it did not mean, \"I accept certain creedal articles of faith.\""},{"time":216000,"text":"It meant: \"I commit myself. I engage myself.\""},{"time":220000,"text":"Indeed, some of the world traditions think very little of religious orthodoxy."},{"time":227000,"text":"In the Quran, religious opinion -- religious orthodoxy -- is dismissed as \"zanna:\""},{"time":233000,"text":"self-indulgent guesswork about matters that nobody can be certain of one way or the other,"},{"time":239000,"text":"but which makes people quarrelsome and stupidly sectarian. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":242000,"text":"So if religion is not about believing things, what is it about?"},{"time":249000,"text":"What I've found, across the board, is that religion is about behaving differently."},{"time":254000,"text":"Instead of deciding whether or not you believe in God, first you do something."},{"time":260000,"text":"You behave in a committed way,"},{"time":261000,"text":"and then you begin to understand the truths of religion."},{"time":265000,"text":"And religious doctrines are meant to be summons to action;"},{"time":272000,"text":"you only understand them when you put them into practice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276000,"text":"Now, pride of place in this practice is given to compassion."},{"time":284000,"text":"And it is an arresting fact that right across the board,"},{"time":289000,"text":"in every single one of the major world faiths, compassion --"},{"time":293000,"text":"the ability to feel with the other in the way we've been thinking about this evening --"},{"time":298000,"text":"is not only the test of any true religiosity, it is also what will bring us"},{"time":306000,"text":"into the presence of what Jews, Christians and Muslims call \"God\" or the \"Divine.\""},{"time":311000,"text":"It is compassion, says the Buddha, which brings you to Nirvana."},{"time":317000,"text":"Why? Because in compassion, when we feel with the other,"},{"time":321000,"text":"we dethrone ourselves from the center of our world and we put"},{"time":326000,"text":"another person there. And once we get rid of ego, then we're ready to see the Divine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334000,"text":"And in particular, every single one of the major world traditions has highlighted -- has said --"},{"time":342000,"text":"and put at the core of their tradition what's become known as the Golden Rule."},{"time":347000,"text":"First propounded by Confucius five centuries before Christ:"},{"time":351000,"text":"\"Do not do to others what you would not like them to do to you.\""},{"time":355000,"text":"That, he said, was the central thread which ran through all his teaching"},{"time":359000,"text":"and that his disciples should put into practice all day and every day."},{"time":364000,"text":"And it was -- the Golden Rule would bring them to the transcendent value that he called \"ren,\""},{"time":369000,"text":"human-heartedness, which was a transcendent experience in itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375000,"text":"And this is absolutely crucial to the monotheisms, too."},{"time":382000,"text":"There's a famous story about the great rabbi, Hillel, the older contemporary of Jesus."},{"time":385000,"text":"A pagan came to him and offered to convert to Judaism if the rabbi could"},{"time":390000,"text":"recite the whole of Jewish teaching while he stood on one leg."},{"time":393000,"text":"Hillel stood on one leg and said, \"That which is hateful to you,"},{"time":397000,"text":"do not do to your neighbor. That is the Torah. The rest is commentary."},{"time":402000,"text":"Go and study it.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":404000,"text":"And \"go and study it\" was what he meant."},{"time":408000,"text":"He said, \"In your exegesis, you must make it clear"},{"time":412000,"text":"that every single verse of the Torah is a commentary, a gloss upon the Golden Rule.\""},{"time":420000,"text":"The great Rabbi Meir said that any interpretation of Scripture which"},{"time":427000,"text":"led to hatred and disdain, or contempt of other people --"},{"time":432000,"text":"any people whatsoever -- was illegitimate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435000,"text":"Saint Augustine made exactly the same point."},{"time":438000,"text":"Scripture, he says, \"teaches nothing but charity, and we must not leave"},{"time":444000,"text":"an interpretation of Scripture until we have found a compassionate interpretation of it.\""},{"time":451000,"text":"And this struggle to find compassion in some of these rather rebarbative texts"},{"time":457000,"text":"is a good dress rehearsal for doing the same in ordinary life. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":463000,"text":"But now look at our world. And we are living in a world that is --"},{"time":470000,"text":"where religion has been hijacked. Where terrorists cite Quranic verses to justify their atrocities."},{"time":481000,"text":"Where instead of taking Jesus' words, \"Love your enemies."},{"time":488000,"text":"Don't judge others,\" we have the spectacle of Christians endlessly judging other people,"},{"time":495000,"text":"endlessly using Scripture as a way of arguing with other people,"},{"time":501000,"text":"putting other people down. Throughout the ages, religion has been used to oppress others,"},{"time":509000,"text":"and this is because of human ego, human greed."},{"time":513000,"text":"We have a talent as a species for messing up wonderful things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518000,"text":"So the traditions also insisted -- and this is an important point, I think --"},{"time":525000,"text":"that you could not and must not confine your compassion"},{"time":528000,"text":"to your own group: your own nation, your own co-religionists,"},{"time":535000,"text":"your own fellow countrymen. You must have what one of the Chinese sages called \"jian ai\":"},{"time":540000,"text":"concern for everybody. Love your enemies. Honor the stranger."},{"time":546000,"text":"We formed you, says the Quran, into tribes and nations so that you may know one another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552000,"text":"And this, again -- this universal outreach -- is getting subdued in the strident use of religion --"},{"time":562000,"text":"abuse of religion -- for nefarious gains."},{"time":568000,"text":"Now, I've lost count of the number of taxi drivers who,"},{"time":572000,"text":"when I say to them what I do for a living, inform me that religion"},{"time":577000,"text":"has been the cause of all the major world wars in history. Wrong."},{"time":581000,"text":"The causes of our present woes are political."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586000,"text":"But, make no mistake about it, religion is a kind of fault line,"},{"time":597000,"text":"and when a conflict gets ingrained in a region, religion can get sucked in"},{"time":601000,"text":"and become part of the problem. Our modernity has been exceedingly violent."},{"time":606000,"text":"Between 1914 and 1945, 70 million people died in Europe alone as a result of armed conflict."},{"time":616000,"text":"And so many of our institutions, even football, which used to be a pleasant pastime,"},{"time":625000,"text":"now causes riots where people even die."},{"time":630000,"text":"And it's not surprising that religion, too, has been affected by this violent ethos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637000,"text":"There's also a great deal, I think, of religious illiteracy around."},{"time":645000,"text":"People seem to think, now equate religious faith with believing things."},{"time":650000,"text":"As though that -- we call religious people often believers,"},{"time":655000,"text":"as though that were the main thing that they do. And very often, secondary goals"},{"time":662000,"text":"get pushed into the first place, in place of compassion and the Golden Rule."},{"time":668000,"text":"Because the Golden Rule is difficult. I sometimes -- when I'm speaking to"},{"time":674000,"text":"congregations about compassion, I sometimes see"},{"time":678000,"text":"a mutinous expression crossing some of their faces because"},{"time":685000,"text":"a lot of religious people prefer to be right, rather than compassionate. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":691000,"text":"Now -- but that's not the whole story."},{"time":695000,"text":"Since September the 11th, when my work on Islam suddenly propelled me"},{"time":701000,"text":"into public life, in a way that I'd never imagined, I've been able to sort of go all over the world,"},{"time":708000,"text":"and finding, everywhere I go, a yearning for change."},{"time":714000,"text":"I've just come back from Pakistan, where literally thousands of people came to my lectures,"},{"time":722000,"text":"because they were yearning, first of all, to hear a friendly Western voice."},{"time":726000,"text":"And especially the young people were coming. And were asking me --"},{"time":733000,"text":"the young people were saying, \"What can we do? What can we do to change things?\""},{"time":738000,"text":"And my hosts in Pakistan said, \"Look, don't be too polite to us."},{"time":745000,"text":"Tell us where we're going wrong. Let's talk together about where religion is failing.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":751000,"text":"Because it seems to me that with -- our current situation is so serious"},{"time":758000,"text":"at the moment that any ideology that doesn't promote a sense of global understanding"},{"time":767000,"text":"and global appreciation of each other is failing the test of the time."},{"time":773000,"text":"And religion, with its wide following ... Here in the United States,"},{"time":779000,"text":"people may be being religious in a different way, as a report has just shown --"},{"time":785000,"text":"but they still want to be religious. It's only Western Europe that has retained its secularism,"},{"time":793000,"text":"which is now beginning to look rather endearingly old-fashioned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796000,"text":"But people want to be religious, and religion should be made"},{"time":803000,"text":"to be a force for harmony in the world, which it can and should be --"},{"time":808000,"text":"because of the Golden Rule."},{"time":811000,"text":"\"Do not do to others what you would not have them do to you\":"},{"time":815000,"text":"an ethos that should now be applied globally."},{"time":818000,"text":"We should not treat other nations as we would not wish to be treated ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"And these -- whatever our wretched beliefs -- is a religious matter, it's a spiritual matter."},{"time":833000,"text":"It's a profound moral matter that engages and should engage us all."},{"time":838000,"text":"And as I say, there is a hunger for change out there."},{"time":842000,"text":"Here in the United States, I think you see it in this election campaign: a longing for change."},{"time":848000,"text":"And people in churches all over and mosques all over this continent after September the 11th,"},{"time":858000,"text":"coming together locally to create networks of understanding."},{"time":864000,"text":"With the mosque, with the synagogue, saying, \"We must start to speak to one another.\""},{"time":869000,"text":"I think it's time that we moved beyond the idea of toleration and move toward appreciation of the other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":880000,"text":"I'd -- there's one story I'd just like to mention."},{"time":885000,"text":"This comes from \"The Iliad.\" But it tells you what this spirituality should be."},{"time":891000,"text":"You know the story of \"The Iliad,\" the 10-year war between Greece and Troy."},{"time":896000,"text":"In one incident, Achilles, the famous warrior of Greece, takes his troops out of the war,"},{"time":901000,"text":"and the whole war effort suffers. And in the course of the ensuing muddle,"},{"time":907000,"text":"his beloved friend, Patroclus, is killed -- and killed in single combat"},{"time":913000,"text":"by one of the Trojan princes, Hector. And Achilles goes mad with grief and rage and revenge,"},{"time":918000,"text":"and he mutilates the body. He kills Hector, he mutilates his body"},{"time":928000,"text":"and then he refuses to give the body back for burial to the family,"},{"time":932000,"text":"which means that, in Greek ethos, Hector's soul will wander eternally, lost."},{"time":939000,"text":"And then one night, Priam, king of Troy, an old man,"},{"time":943000,"text":"comes into the Greek camp incognito, makes his way to Achilles' tent"},{"time":948000,"text":"to ask for the body of his son."},{"time":951000,"text":"And everybody is shocked when the old man takes off his head covering and shows himself."},{"time":958000,"text":"And Achilles looks at him and thinks of his father. And he starts to weep."},{"time":966000,"text":"And Priam looks at the man who has murdered so many of his sons,"},{"time":970000,"text":"and he, too, starts to weep. And the sound of their weeping filled the house."},{"time":975000,"text":"The Greeks believed that weeping together created a bond between people."},{"time":980000,"text":"And then Achilles takes the body of Hector, he hands it very tenderly to the father,"},{"time":988000,"text":"and the two men look at each other, and see each other as divine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":993000,"text":"That is the ethos found, too, in all the religions."},{"time":1001000,"text":"It's what is meant by overcoming the horror that we feel when we are under threat of our enemies,"},{"time":1007000,"text":"and beginning to appreciate the other."},{"time":1010000,"text":"It's of great importance that the word for \"holy\" in Hebrew, applied to God, is \"Kadosh\": separate, other."},{"time":1019000,"text":"And it is often, perhaps, the very otherness of our enemies which can"},{"time":1025000,"text":"give us intimations of that utterly mysterious transcendence which is God."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1031000,"text":"And now, here's my wish:"},{"time":1034000,"text":"I wish that you would help with the creation,"},{"time":1040000,"text":"launch and propagation of a Charter for Compassion,"},{"time":1046000,"text":"crafted by a group of inspirational thinkers from"},{"time":1052000,"text":"the three Abrahamic traditions of Judaism, Christianity and Islam,"},{"time":1056000,"text":"and based on the fundamental principle of the Golden Rule."},{"time":1061000,"text":"We need to create a movement among all these people that I meet in my travels --"},{"time":1069000,"text":"you probably meet, too -- who want to join up, in some way,"},{"time":1073000,"text":"and reclaim their faith, which they feel, as I say, has been hijacked."},{"time":1078000,"text":"We need to empower people to remember the compassionate ethos,"},{"time":1084000,"text":"and to give guidelines. This Charter would not be a massive document."},{"time":1088000,"text":"I'd like to see it -- to give guidelines as to how to interpret the Scriptures,"},{"time":1096000,"text":"these texts that are being abused. Remember what the rabbis and what Augustine"},{"time":1102000,"text":"said about how Scripture should be governed by the principle of charity."},{"time":1105000,"text":"Let's get back to that. And the idea, too, of Jews, Christians and Muslims --"},{"time":1111000,"text":"these traditions now so often at loggerheads -- working together to"},{"time":1116000,"text":"create a document which we hope will be signed by a thousand, at least,"},{"time":1123000,"text":"of major religious leaders from all the traditions of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1127000,"text":"And you are the people. I'm just a solitary scholar."},{"time":1131000,"text":"Despite the idea that I love a good time, which I was rather amazed to see coming up on me"},{"time":1137000,"text":"-- I actually spend a great deal of time alone, studying, and I'm not very --"},{"time":1143000,"text":"you're the people with media knowledge to explain to me how we can get this to everybody,"},{"time":1150000,"text":"everybody on the planet. I've had some preliminary talks,"},{"time":1154000,"text":"and Archbishop Desmond Tutu, for example,"},{"time":1157000,"text":"is very happy to give his name to this, as is Imam Feisal Rauf, the Imam in New York City."},{"time":1167000,"text":"Also, I would be working with the Alliance of Civilizations at the United Nations."},{"time":1175000,"text":"I was part of that United Nations initiative called the Alliance of Civilizations,"},{"time":1183000,"text":"which was asked by Kofi Annan to diagnose the causes of extremism,"},{"time":1189000,"text":"and to give practical guidelines to member states about how to avoid the escalation of further extremism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1198000,"text":"And the Alliance has told me that they are very happy to work with it."},{"time":1202000,"text":"The importance of this is that this is -- I can see some of you starting to look worried,"},{"time":1208000,"text":"because you think it's a slow and cumbersome body --"},{"time":1211000,"text":"but what the United Nations can do is give us some neutrality,"},{"time":1214000,"text":"so that this isn't seen as a Western or a Christian initiative, but that it's coming,"},{"time":1220000,"text":"as it were, from the United Nations, from the world --"},{"time":1223000,"text":"who would help with the sort of bureaucracy of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1229000,"text":"And so I do urge you to join me in making -- in this charter --"},{"time":1235000,"text":"to building this charter, launching it and propagating it so that it becomes --"},{"time":1243000,"text":"I'd like to see it in every college, every church, every mosque, every synagogue in the world,"},{"time":1252000,"text":"so that people can look at their tradition, reclaim it, and make religion a source of peace in the world,"},{"time":1261000,"text":"which it can and should be. Thank you very much. (Applause)"}]}]}